Explanation:

The solution uses a while loop to iterate until the number becomes 0. In each iteration, it calculates the remainder of the number divided by 2 and appends it to the result string, starting from the rightmost digit. After appending the digit, the number is divided by 2 to move to the next digit. This process continues until the number becomes 0, resulting in a binary representation of the number in base -2. The solution has a time complexity of O(log(n)) due to the iterative approach, and a space complexity of O(1) as the result string only grows linearly with the number of digits. The energy implications are low as the solution only performs basic arithmetic operations and string manipulation.

